# Frontend Architecture Rules

## Components
- Functional components ONLY — no class components
- Every component that receives the same props must produce the same output → use `React.memo`
- react-flow custom nodes MUST be wrapped in `React.memo` — re-renders kill graph performance
- Props interfaces defined in the same file, exported with `I` prefix convention: `IUserNodeProps`
- No logic in JSX — extract to named functions or hooks

## Hooks
- Complex hook logic (more than 5 lines) extracted to `use{Name}.ts` files
- Hooks directory: `src/hooks/`
- Never call React Query hooks inside loops or conditions

## State Management
- Zustand store for global UI state (selected nodes, filters, layout mode)
- React Query for all server state (API data, loading, error)
- Local `useState` for ephemeral component state only (dropdown open/closed)
- Never mix: don't cache server data in Zustand

## react-flow Rules
- Import from `@xyflow/react` (v12+), not the old `reactflow`
- Custom node types registered in `nodeTypes` object OUTSIDE the component render — never inline
- Custom edge types registered in `edgeTypes` OUTSIDE render
- Use `useNodesState` / `useEdgesState` for node/edge state
- dagre layout computed ONCE when graph data changes, not on every render

## Styling
- Tailwind CSS utility classes only — no inline styles, no CSS modules (React Flow edge labels may use `style` for transform/position where required)
- Theme: `ThemeProvider` + `useTheme()`; `class="dark"` on `<html>` toggles CSS variables in `src/index.css` / `tailwind.config.ts`. Preference key: `aclara-theme` (localStorage). Light is default.
- Semantic colors: prefer `bg-page`, `bg-panel`, `text-ink-*`, `text-ink-on-warning-soft`, `border-line-*`, `brand.*`, `status.*` — not raw Tailwind palette (`amber-*`, etc.) or ad hoc hex in JSX
- Responsive not required for POC — optimize for 1280px+ desktop

## API Layer
- All API calls via React Query hooks in `src/api/aclara.api.ts`
- Never call `fetch` directly in components
- Query keys are centralized constants: `QUERY_KEYS.graph(project)`, etc.
- Show loading skeletons, not spinners, for initial data fetch

## Project-First Flow
- On app load: fetch project list, show project selector
- No data fetches run until a project is selected
- Selected project stored in Zustand, passed as param to all other hooks